data.enText: to produce new leaves or buds ; to start to grow
new leaves sprouting from the trees

data.chText: 这些种子几天后就会发芽。
data.enText: The seeds will sprout in a few days.
to appear; to develop sth, especially in large numbers

data.chText: 一夜之间长出来好几百朵蘑菇。
data.enText: Hundreds of mushrooms had sprouted up overnight.

data.chText: 最近几年，城里涌现出不少购物中心、迪斯科舞厅和夜总会。
data.enText: The town has sprouted shopping malls, discos and nightclubs in recent years.
to start to grow sth; to start to grow on sb/sth

data.chText: 我们上次见到蒂姆以后，蒂姆长出了胡子。
data.enText: Tim has sprouted a beard since we last saw him.
a new part growing on a plant

ex.enText: It was springtime and the fruit trees were in bud.

ex.chText: 他知道怎样让无花果嫩枝成活。
ex.enText: He knew the tips for growing a fig tree from a shoot.

synonyms.bx: 指植物刚长出的新枝、嫩枝或嫩芽。

ex.enText: The wheat sprouts are growing very evenly.

synonyms.bx: 指蔬菜、种子、植物的嫩芽、嫩苗等。

tr: a newly grown bud (especially from a germinating seed)
any new growth of a plant such as a new branch or a bud
put forth and grow sprouts or shoots
example: the plant sprouted early this year

value.def: When plants, vegetables, or seeds sprout, they produce new shoots or leaves.

example.ex: It only takes a few days for beans to sprout.
example.tran: 豆子只要几天就能发芽。

value.tran: (植物、蔬菜、种子)发芽，抽芽，长芽

value.def: When leaves, shoots, or plants sprout somewhere, they grow there.

example.ex: Leaf-shoots were beginning to sprout on the hawthorn...
example.tran: 山楂树上开始长出叶芽。

example.ex: Birch trees sprouted from the rubble and grew into a dense young wood.
example.tran: 桦树从瓦砾中长出来，形成了一片茂密的新林。

value.def: If a garden or other area of land sprouts plants, they start to grow there.

example.ex: ...the garden, which had had time to sprout a shocking collection of weeds.
example.tran: 久而久之便野草丛生的花园

value.def: If you sprout beans or seeds, you make them grow small shoots before eating them. You usually do this by soaking them in water.

example.ex: When you sprout seeds their nutritional content increases...
example.tran: 让种子发芽后，其营养含量会提高。

example.ex: Sprouted beans only need to be cooked for 1-2 minutes.
example.tran: 豆芽只需烹炒一到两分钟。

value.tran: (出于食用目的)使(豆子、种子等)发芽

value.def: If something such as hair sprouts from a person or animal, or if they sprout it, it grows on them.

example.ex: She is very old now, with little, round, wire-rimmed glasses and whiskers sprouting from her chin...
example.tran: 她现在很老了，戴着圆圆的金属架小眼镜，下巴上还长出了胡须。

example.ex: As well as sprouting a few grey hairs, Kevin seems to be suffering the occasional memory loss.
example.tran: 除长出了些许白发外，凯文似乎还患上了间歇性失忆。

value.def: If a large number of things have appeared or developed somewhere, you can say that they have sprouted there or that the place has sprouted them.

example.ex: More than a million satellite dishes have sprouted on homes across the country...
example.tran: 100 多万个卫星接收器迅速出现在了全国各地的家庭用户中。

example.ex: Since its first shop was opened in 1976, it has sprouted outlets in 39 countries.
example.tran: 自从 1976 年开设第一家店以来，它已经在 39 个国家里开设了大量分店。

value.def: Sprouts are vegetables that look like tiny cabbages. They are also called brussels sprouts .

example.ex: After eleven days of growth the number of sprouts was counted.
example.tran: 经过11天的生长后，对新芽的数量进行了计数。
